Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.02,0:00:08.48,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.40,0:00:11.19,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,I'll investigate here, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.81,0:00:13.99,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,I'll contact you again later.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.83,0:00:16.43,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Um, Rieze?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.05,0:00:20.54,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,I-I'm sorry...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.54,0:00:21.59,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,It's nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.95,0:00:23.37,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,I know this is an important time.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.71,0:00:28.35,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,You don't need to put up a brave front.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.55,0:00:35.86,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Would you like to tell me what happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.33,0:02:11.86,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Takayama's weapon went out of control?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.86,0:02:14.53,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,And Crusty disappeared?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.59,0:02:18.24,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,He's missing, and he isn't \Nresponding to telepathy.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.83,0:02:21.41,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,We also have that murderer to think about.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.41,0:02:26.25,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Until more details are known, \ND.D.D. doesn't want word to get out.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.46,0:02:31.25,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, it may be best to wait \Nbefore we tell the Round Table.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.02,0:02:34.46,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,There are Minami spies around, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.87,0:02:37.15,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,We shouldn't tell Princess Lenessia, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.83,0:02:39.01,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.41,0:02:45.37,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Knowing Crusty, he'll come right \Nback, as if nothing happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.92,0:02:47.27,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.74,0:02:52.01,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Henrietta, big trouble!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.01,0:02:53.44,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.78,0:02:56.58,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,I need to talk to you about the flavor text.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.96,0:03:03.66,Title,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(1302,1)}The Maidens of Watermaple
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.06,0:03:01.80,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,The Maidens of Watermaple.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.42,0:03:06.56,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,The flavor text is becoming real?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.56,0:03:10.11,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. Originally, it was just backstories for items.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.11,0:03:14.42,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,But now, the stuff in the text is \Ncoming true or happening in reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.74,0:03:19.55,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Then we'll also need to be mindful \Nof the flavor text in the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.99,0:03:23.05,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, we don't know what will happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.58,0:03:27.31,Default - italics,R,0000,0000,0000,,Which means Misa's weapon's going out of control
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.04,0:03:30.56,Default - italics,R,0000,0000,0000,,might be related to that.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.47,0:03:32.35,Default - italics,R,0000,0000,0000,,And...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.07,0:03:35.24,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,The murderer's Byakumaru...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.69,0:03:39.13,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Its flavor text might have become real, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.11,0:03:43.09,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,That means the murderer possesses \Nnot only a Royal Guard's armor,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.09,0:03:45.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but a powerful weapon, as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.08,0:03:50.25,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Byakumaru is a raid drop, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.59,0:03:54.24,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, it's from a raid monster in \Nthe tenth expansion pack,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.57,0:03:56.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the Death Warrior Rugrius.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.44,0:04:00.58,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,It was his katana.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.58,0:04:02.18,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Rugrius?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.18,0:04:05.39,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,What does its flavor text say?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.68,0:04:09.05,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,It describes the legend of Rugrius, \Nand how he became a monster.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.36,0:04:13.19,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,He was originally one of the Izumo \NKnights, a hero of the Ice Wall,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.25,0:04:15.40,Location,R,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(792,896)\an9\fs17}Legend/ Graupel Sword Byakumaru \N\NThe favorite sword of Rugrius, \Nthe hero of Ezzo who drove the giants \Nto the Jade Garden. This blade freezes \Neverything, and contains the rage of the \Nhero who met his death at the betrayal \Nof the Daughter of Elm, Sutu Inaw.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.19,0:04:14.86,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,who fought for a century.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.73,0:04:19.36,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,He fought to protect the happiness \Nof the people of Susukino,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.59,0:04:22.28,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,and he drove away the evil giants.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.41,0:04:26.20,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,He was truly the Ezzo Empire's hero.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.09,0:04:27.87,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.71,0:04:34.89,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,He was betrayed by the Daughter of Elm,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.89,0:04:37.54,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Sutu Inaw, and poisoned to death.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.32,0:04:43.97,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,So, as a raid monster, Rugrius was \Ndescribed as angry and hateful.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.31,0:04:46.61,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,That's quite a dark story.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.17,0:04:49.29,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Then that hateful spirit has become real,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.29,0:04:51.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and is giving the murderer power?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.39,0:04:53.27,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,That's ridiculous!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.93,0:04:57.44,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,S-Sorry, I just...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.13,0:05:02.82,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,If that's the case, we can use it \Nto our advantage in our planning.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.64,0:05:19.19,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,No... No!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.80,0:05:23.98,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not Rugrius!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.98,0:05:26.09,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I am a proud Defender!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.43,0:05:28.81,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,That's right, Nelreth.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.26,0:05:32.10,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,You aren't the town guard dog.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.48,0:05:38.04,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,You are a chosen hero, with the \Npower to surpass the adventurers.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.51,0:05:42.11,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Together, we shall avenge ourselves \Nupon the Daughter of Elm
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.11,0:05:44.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and the humans...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.80,0:05:57.26,Default - italics,A,0000,0000,0000,,The flavor text is becoming real.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.52,0:06:03.00,Default - italics,A,0000,0000,0000,,If I'd had Byakumaru, what would \Nhave happened to me?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.61,0:06:09.25,Default - italics,A,0000,0000,0000,,With that ugly jealousy I felt toward Minori...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.60,0:06:15.10,HUD1,A,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8\c&H2B3636&\3c&H8E9EA4&}Amenoma
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.85,0:06:29.78,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Are you sure?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.00,0:06:34.28,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I think it's better to stay out of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.21,0:06:39.12,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,His little friend will find the answer on her own.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.53,0:06:42.10,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Will it really be in the Teachings?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.09,0:06:45.16,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.46,0:06:49.77,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,They are mere teachings, \Nbut they are the Teachings.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.04,0:06:56.14,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I believe in the strength of girls.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.07,0:07:06.88,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, we're going to begin training.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.88,0:07:09.65,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Our goal is to take out the murderer.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.92,0:07:13.91,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,In accordance with Rieze's plan, \Nthe raid teams will train
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.91,0:07:16.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to learn about each other and fight effectively.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.10,0:07:18.27,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.27,0:07:20.60,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,She wants to know the Teachings.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.12,0:07:23.54,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone teach her what you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.36,0:07:30.55,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Um, I don't have much to offer, \Nbut I look forward to our time together.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.99,0:07:36.27,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,That sounds like you want to get married!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.27,0:07:39.43,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,If Henrietta heard that, she'd be freaking out!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.98,0:07:43.25,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,We want to be strong, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.33,0:07:48.72,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Let's all do our best, Akatsuki!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.92,0:07:54.72,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Feels good to say what's on your mind, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.66,0:07:57.05,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Is everyone ready?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.05,0:08:01.00,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,First, you need to be able \Nto judge distance by sight.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.35,0:08:03.12,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Teachings? I'm not sure...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.45,0:08:05.58,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Anything you know would help. Please.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.02,0:08:12.94,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,It's not something you can get by \Nclearing a raid or getting an item...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.94,0:08:13.97,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.34,0:08:16.80,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,It's nothing that special.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.35,0:08:20.80,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,And it's not something you can just teach someone.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.27,0:08:30.01,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,For example, our guild master's Teachings \Ngive him an ability called Eyes of the Void.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.10,0:08:36.53,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,It lets him visualize a target's HP and \Nstatus, even if he can't see them.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.96,0:08:39.03,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,With this ability,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.03,0:08:44.14,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I can know the HP of players \Nbehind me, so it's pretty handy.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.14,0:08:45.51,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,I see!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.51,0:08:49.59,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,But only the guild master can do it,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.03,0:08:53.09,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,so I don't know if you can learn it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.78,0:08:58.10,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,That's fine! Teach me anyway!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.26,0:09:09.27,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Again!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.08,0:09:23.13,Default - italics,A,0000,0000,0000,,The Teachings...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.64,0:09:26.11,Default - italics,A,0000,0000,0000,,If only I had more of a clue.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.50,0:09:27.67,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Akatsuki!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.94,0:09:32.13,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,This is especially for you!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.86,0:09:34.09,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Especially?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.11,0:09:40.60,Bento,,0000,0000,0000,,You {\c&H336C3E&}Can {\c&H5B88CB&}Do {\c&HA0E6E8&}It
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.57,0:09:48.60,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,The murderer is a Person of the Land,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.96,0:09:53.50,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,and since he was a Royal Guard, \Nhe has the movable armor's power.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.93,0:09:56.11,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,And the Graupel Sword Byakumaru, as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.51,0:10:01.62,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,With normal attacks, the Byakumaru \Ncan deal blizzard and cold damage.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.89,0:10:04.37,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Rugrius was a raid boss, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.81,0:10:05.91,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.91,0:10:07.85,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Taking that into account,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.85,0:10:11.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,with the flavor text now becoming \Nreal, it has three effects.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.36,0:10:15.63,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,First, freeze status from the blizzard.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.05,0:10:20.69,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Second, all of his stats are buffed for \Nevery additional person he fights.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.19,0:10:25.27,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,For every adventurer within fifty meters,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.56,0:10:28.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,his attack and defense increase.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.45,0:10:34.40,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Then we can't all fight him at once, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.75,0:10:36.68,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,So the plan is...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.68,0:10:41.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Instead of six-member raid teams, \Nwe'll use teams of two or three.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.50,0:10:44.24,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,We'll deploy them around Akihabara like a net.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.80,0:10:46.91,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,We'll need twenty-four people.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.31,0:10:49.92,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,A full raid in Akihabara, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.68,0:10:52.54,Default - italics,L,0000,0000,0000,,Rieze is amazing...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.54,0:10:56.92,Default - italics,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd heard she was the leader of \NCrusty's guild's training division,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.43,0:11:01.68,Default - italics,L,0000,0000,0000,,but she's explaining her strategy to these \Nmen without the slightest hesitation.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.08,0:11:04.91,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Aren't those teams a little too small?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.25,0:11:06.31,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,How will you coordinate them?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.63,0:11:10.31,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,We'll use the raid party chat for communication.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.83,0:11:16.06,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,They'll be distributed so that they can \Nmove in as soon as the target is found.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.06,0:11:19.81,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,So, what is Byakumaru's third effect?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.40,0:11:21.20,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,What I think it is?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.57,0:11:22.40,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.75,0:11:24.72,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,A huge boost to his HP.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.10,0:11:27.37,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Depending on the number of people in the zone,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.37,0:11:30.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,his max HP will change greatly.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.73,0:11:33.00,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,That's another troublesome one.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.55,0:11:35.34,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Then what's the plan?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.82,0:11:40.57,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,I'd like to issue a curfew confining people \Nto their homes until New Year's.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.18,0:11:46.85,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Please have the Round Table ask the \NPeople of the Land to stay inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.28,0:11:49.85,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Well, we can do it, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.56,0:11:52.85,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Will it really work?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.21,0:11:54.55,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.83,0:12:00.11,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,If he has movable armor, he can \Nteleport through Akihabara.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.68,0:12:02.59,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,If he runs, we can't do anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.00,0:12:04.45,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,The key to that
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.41,0:12:07.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,is in Princess Lenessia's hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.52,0:12:24.18,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,You want me to cut off the power \Nto the large magic circle?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.18,0:12:24.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.85,0:12:29.95,Default - flashback,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Of course, if we shut off the magic supply,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.95,0:12:32.13,Default - flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,the movable armor would cease to function.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.63,0:12:36.82,Default - flashback,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,But at the same time, it would \Ndisable the city's magic defenses,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.82,0:12:39.25,Default - flashback,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,allowing monsters to enter the city.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.89,0:12:41.98,Default - flashback,L,0000,0000,0000,,C-Can't you reboot it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.98,0:12:45.07,Default - flashback,L,0000,0000,0000,,You can't just turn it back on?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.87,0:12:49.99,Default - flashback,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,All I can say is that it would take decades.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.88,0:12:56.45,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,I'm well aware of the risks.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.42,0:13:01.92,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,If you accept, Lenessia... Princess...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.34,0:13:04.43,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,The mission might succeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.43,0:13:06.34,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,No, I'll make it succeed!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.58,0:13:12.83,Default,L,0000,0000,0000,,Does that mean you're asking \Nme in my official capacity?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.85,0:13:16.35,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,I believe it does.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.02,0:13:20.74,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,No matter what your answer,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.74,0:13:22.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,if it's your will as the princess, \Nno one will blame you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.16,0:13:26.67,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Even if you refuse, it won't affect \Nyour friendships with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.04,0:13:28.78,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,There's nothing to worry about.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.94,0:13:42.82,Default - italics,L,0000,0000,0000,,In the end, I couldn't say whether I'd do it or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.28,0:13:48.42,Default - italics,L,0000,0000,0000,,As their friend, I want to do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.70,0:13:53.06,Default - italics,L,0000,0000,0000,,But as the Marquis's ambassador...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.41,0:13:55.63,Default - italics,L,0000,0000,0000,,What should I do?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.96,0:14:03.95,Default - italics,A,0000,0000,0000,,There isn't much time left.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.29,0:14:05.35,Default - italics,A,0000,0000,0000,,What should I do?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.83,0:14:09.07,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,How's it coming along?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.81,0:14:12.51,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,When's the operation?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.66,0:14:14.78,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,New Year's Eve.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.35,0:14:16.65,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.65,0:14:20.08,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Solve the year's problems \Nbefore the year ends, yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.62,0:14:25.09,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,I want to learn the Teachings, \Nbut I still don't know anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.47,0:14:29.79,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Is there anything I can do?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.23,0:14:31.50,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.50,0:14:32.60,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,I'm all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.28,0:14:34.48,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.92,0:14:39.10,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,But I think you may be trying a bit too hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.68,0:14:44.61,Default - flashback,A,0000,0000,0000,,My lord, why not take a break?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.24,0:14:46.28,Default - flashback,S,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.85,0:14:49.11,Default - flashback,S,0000,0000,0000,,But I want to do everything I can.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.59,0:14:51.62,Default - flashback,A,0000,0000,0000,,But you don't have to push yourself too hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.75,0:14:54.50,Default - flashback,S,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not pushing myself too hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.50,0:14:56.33,Default - flashback,S,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(1,476)}I can try hard because I want to.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.86,0:15:01.88,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know why my lord is trying so hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.28,0:15:04.85,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,But he is.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.26,0:15:07.50,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,So I'll do my best, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.40,0:15:12.39,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,I can't worry about my own pride \Nif I want to defeat the murderer.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.01,0:15:15.39,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Because I'm weak.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.19,0:15:22.25,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, keep your distance, and go around.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.25,0:15:23.90,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Don't let those buffs wear off.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.39,0:15:27.21,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,What's important is to truly know your enemy.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.63,0:15:32.77,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Know exactly what they can \Nand what they can't do.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.77,0:15:37.73,Default - italics,A,0000,0000,0000,,I'm weak.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.72,0:15:39.37,Default - italics,A,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.90,0:15:43.14,Default - italics,A,0000,0000,0000,,There are things you can only learn \Nby accepting your weakness.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.84,0:15:47.91,Default - italics,A,0000,0000,0000,,Being weak, losing... \NThese aren't pointless things.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.15,0:15:52.05,Default - italics,A,0000,0000,0000,,I can't do anything on my own.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.41,0:15:53.22,Default - italics,A,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.76,0:15:56.04,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Akatsuki, do you use these?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.44,0:15:58.38,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,They're good for defense.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.03,0:16:00.23,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.67,0:16:03.54,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Here, have some strawberries, Akatsuki.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.32,0:16:07.52,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,We got lots to make Christmas cakes, \Nbut we had some leftover.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.07,0:16:09.10,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.72,0:16:12.78,Default - italics,A,0000,0000,0000,,I can become strong with everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.59,0:16:16.40,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,You are small...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.12,0:16:18.87,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,But that's actually an advantage.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.35,0:16:22.21,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,He's huge, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.21,0:16:25.38,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,He won't be able to keep up \Nif you dance all around him.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.66,0:16:27.63,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,It makes it easy to get in his blind spots.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.05,0:16:30.88,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Let's try.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.03,0:16:38.43,Default - italics,A,0000,0000,0000,,I've always been ashamed of my height.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.84,0:16:41.43,Default - italics,A,0000,0000,0000,,But I never thought that weakness \Ncould also be a strength.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.39,0:16:45.69,Default - italics,A,0000,0000,0000,,Know exactly what they can and can't do!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.13,0:16:48.90,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,This is it!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.89,0:16:52.65,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,You're training to defeat the murderer, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.94,0:16:54.36,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,I heard about it from Michitaka,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.65,0:16:58.65,SignC,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,{\an7}Seine/ Adventurer
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.65,0:16:58.65,SignD,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Shironiji/ Adventurer
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.36,0:16:56.20,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,and decided I wanted to help.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.01,0:16:58.66,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Are you still recruiting?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.04,0:17:00.22,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.56,0:17:03.04,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,What about you, Seine?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.42,0:17:05.04,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.30,0:17:10.92,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Nah, it's nothing...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.18,0:17:13.76,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,This gives us twenty-four members.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.76,0:17:17.06,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,I'll ask you to take care of that other matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.50,0:17:19.12,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,As a twenty-fifth member.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.71,0:17:20.93,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.49,0:17:34.52,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,I'm so happy you came, Princess Lenessia!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.33,0:17:37.65,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Mikakage, are the rice balls ready?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.51,0:17:40.54,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, right. It's lunchtime already, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.54,0:17:42.40,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,It's hardly "already"...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.86,0:17:45.15,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,If you don't hurry, you won't make it in time.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.15,0:17:46.47,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.47,0:17:47.79,Default,L,0000,0000,0000,,U-Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.25,0:17:50.63,Default,L,0000,0000,0000,,Please let me help with something.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.94,0:17:52.81,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? You, Princess?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.15,0:17:54.88,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Do you have the cooking skill?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.27,0:17:58.01,Default,L,0000,0000,0000,,Eh? Um, I don't know...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.30,0:18:00.48,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Want to try?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.56,0:18:09.64,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,I'm starved.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.64,0:18:11.15,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Let's dig in.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.15,0:18:12.79,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Let's eat!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.01,0:18:26.65,Default,L,0000,0000,0000,,May I sit here?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.68,0:18:28.88,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.68,0:18:33.45,Default,L,0000,0000,0000,,I made that.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.87,0:18:39.80,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,It doesn't look like much, but it's good.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.35,0:18:41.50,Default,L,0000,0000,0000,,I'm glad.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.42,0:18:46.71,Default,L,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.00,0:18:50.52,Default,L,0000,0000,0000,,I thought it was convenient for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.52,0:18:51.61,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,What was?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.92,0:18:56.57,Default,L,0000,0000,0000,,When you tried to defeat \Nthe murderer that day.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.96,0:18:58.89,Default,L,0000,0000,0000,,It was only for a second,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.89,0:19:02.15,Default,L,0000,0000,0000,,but I thought that if you defeated the murderer,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.69,0:19:06.25,Default,L,0000,0000,0000,,I could avoid a conflict between \Nadventurers and People of the Land.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.84,0:19:12.86,Default,L,0000,0000,0000,,I thought of crying to my grandfather or to Crusty.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.30,0:19:16.09,Default,L,0000,0000,0000,,But that would be no different from before.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.67,0:19:21.34,Default,L,0000,0000,0000,,I'd just be avoiding responsibility, \Nlike the man from the Kunie
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.34,0:19:23.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,who told me about this.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.35,0:19:28.15,Default,L,0000,0000,0000,,But I'm still uneasy.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.65,0:19:30.33,Default,L,0000,0000,0000,,I can't make a decision.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.95,0:19:33.11,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,When you said I was your friend,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.67,0:19:34.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it made me happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.37,0:19:37.78,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know why you're uneasy,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.78,0:19:39.38,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,but everyone is here.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.77,0:19:40.87,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,I'm here.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.34,0:19:42.42,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,I'm your friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.86,0:19:44.01,Default,L,0000,0000,0000,,Akatsuki...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.12,0:19:47.83,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, we're going to get started!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.83,0:19:48.87,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.79,0:19:55.98,Default,L,0000,0000,0000,,Friends...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.77,0:20:05.11,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Well?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.11,0:20:06.68,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Getting close to figuring something out?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.00,0:20:13.29,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,The real Teaching is being able to \Nsay that Teachings are stupid.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.01,0:20:19.12,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Tatara?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.76,0:20:22.97,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,If I'd known...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.85,0:20:31.74,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,I never would have sold it to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.23,0:20:33.76,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Of course not. I know that.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.27,0:20:35.23,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone does.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.81,0:20:43.63,Default - italics,L,0000,0000,0000,,I can't run away.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.06,0:20:47.06,Default - italics,L,0000,0000,0000,,If I turn this over to someone \Nelse because I'm weak,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.06,0:20:51.11,Default - italics,L,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be admitting that I'm not \Nonly weak, but also inferior.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.19,0:20:54.18,Default - italics,L,0000,0000,0000,,I couldn't be their friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.78,0:20:59.07,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Princess Lenessia...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.75,0:21:01.57,Default,L,0000,0000,0000,,Please let me participate, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.25,0:21:06.12,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,You'll be the twenty-sixth maiden of Watermaple.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.35,0:21:11.58,SignC,H,0000,0000,0000,,{\an9\fad(320,1)}Ringing Blade Haganemushi
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.35,0:21:11.58,SignE,H,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(320,1)}Legend/ {\fs16}Ringing Blade Haganemushi \N\NA legendary short sword that causes any armor it \Nstrikes to instantly rust away, earning it the name \NHaganemushi, or "metal-eating bug." Any blade \Nit clashes against grows duller with each blow.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.17,0:21:22.82,Default - italics,A,0000,0000,0000,,In the end, I didn't learn a single Teaching.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.36,0:21:25.33,Default - italics,A,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.32,0:21:28.27,Default - italics,,0000,0000,0000,,Now I have everyone with me!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.19,0:21:34.35,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Off you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.81,0:21:36.50,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Let's do this!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.50,0:21:37.86,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.88,0:21:42.41,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,It's finally time.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.15,0:21:46.36,Default,L,0000,0000,0000,,Time to smash faces.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.80,0:22:02.92,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Just two?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.75,0:22:08.49,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I've been underestimated...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.67,0:22:11.81,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,It's not enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.10,0:22:15.85,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Gather many subjects,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.85,0:22:17.57,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,make them kneel,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.57,0:22:19.65,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,and take their lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.99,0:22:22.80,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,The Daughter of Elm...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.22,0:22:25.83,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,The humans who betrayed me...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.15,0:22:28.20,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I'll destroy them all!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.49,0:22:29.44,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.93,0:24:08.72,Default,Preview,0000,0000,0000,,At last, the raid begins.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.72,0:24:11.13,Default,Preview,0000,0000,0000,,The murderer's blade shines within the blizzard.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.13,0:24:14.29,Default,Preview,0000,0000,0000,,Akatsuki fights, thinking of \Nthe twenty-sixth maiden.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.29,0:24:17.20,Default,Preview,0000,0000,0000,,But her blade shatters, and her \Nfate is about to be sealed.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.61,0:24:21.69,Default,Preview,0000,0000,0000,,When despair rules the town, \Nthe twenty-seventh maiden appears.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.69,0:24:24.44,Default,Preview,0000,0000,0000,,Akatsuki's Teaching is about to be unleashed.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.77,0:24:26.28,Default,Next time,0000,0000,0000,,Next time: Akihabara Raid.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.77,0:24:30.94,Title,Next time,0000,0000,0000,,Akihabara Raid
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.71,0:24:28.55,Default,Next time,0000,0000,0000,,Rise up once more.
